Round 1

[Patient] "What foods can I eat to help my heart failure?"
[Educator] "Choose low-sodium foods like fruits, veggies, and lean meats."

Round 2

[Patient] "Are there any specific foods I should avoid?"
[Educator] "Limit salty foods like chips, canned soups, and processed meats."

Round 3

[Patient] "Can I still enjoy some soul food dishes?"
[Educator] "Try healthier versions like baked chicken instead of fried."

Round 4

[Patient] "What about drinks? Any recommendations?"
[Educator] "Drink water instead of sugary drinks like soda or sweet tea."

Round 5

[Patient] "Any snack ideas that are heart-friendly?"
[Educator] "Opt for unsalted nuts, yogurt, or whole grain crackers for snacks."